That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    St. Leonard Hythe. See also Table 2, note (g).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Folkestone 
    and Hythe.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Folkestone in Sandgate 
    Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Folkestone.
Abolished 25.3.1886 and added to the parish of Folkestone.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of St. Leonard Hythe, Cheriton, 
    Saltwood, Burmarsh, Sandgate, Lympne and Aldington. See also Table 2, note 
    (g).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Cheriton in Sandgate 
    Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Folkestone 
    and Hythe.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Hythe, 
    Burmarsh and Lympne. See also Table 2, notes (c) and (g).
